In fiscal 2024 (year ended December 31, 2024), approximately 20% of Cloudflare's (NYSE: NET) business was derived from channel partners.

Details and reasoning:
- Cloudflare's fiscal 2024 Form 10-K (filed February 20, 2025) does not disclose a percentage of customers by count derived from channel partners. Instead, it quantifies channel partner contribution by revenue in the "Disaggregation of Revenue" table (Note 3 to the consolidated financial statements), which summarizes "revenue from contracts by type of customer":
  - Channel partners: $337.394 million = 20% of revenue (FY2024), up from 16% in FY2023 ($202.404 million) and 13% in FY2022 ($122.522 million)
  - Direct customers: $1,332.232 million = 80% of revenue (FY2024)
  - Total revenue: $1,669.626 million
- Calculation check: $337,394 / $1,669,626 = 20.21%, which rounds to the 20% disclosed by the company.

Therefore, in fiscal 2024, 20% (precisely 20.21%) of Cloudflare's revenue came from customers derived through channel partners (managed service providers, resellers, distributors, and global system integrators), with the remaining ~80% from direct customers.

